MemberSignature.Value: .method public static hidebysig valuetype System.Guid GetRelativeImportanceComplement(valuetype System.Guid relativeImportanceValue) cil managed
Public Shared Function GetRelativeImportanceComplement (relativeImportanceValue As Guid) As Guid

Docs.param: GUID of the relative importance item.
Docs.summary: Gets the GUID of the complement (the additive inverse) of the relative importance.
Docs.returns: Returns the GUID of the opposite relative importance value.

remarks.para: For example, if is RELATIVE_IMPORTANCE_MODERATE_LESS_LT_STRUCT_UID, the GetRelativeImportanceComplement method returns RELATIVE_IMPORTANCE_MODERATE_MORE_LT_STRUCT_UID.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public static hidebysig char[] INVALID_LT_NAME_CHARS() cil managed
Public Shared Function INVALID_LT_NAME_CHARS () As Char()

Docs.summary: Gets invalid characters for lookup table names.
Docs.returns: Array of the left square bracket '[' and right square bracket ']' characters, which are invalid in lookup table names.

remarks.para: The '[' and ']' characters are not valid in lookup table names because they break formulas.

MemberSignature.Value: .method public static hidebysig bool IsTextMaskSequence(valuetype Microsoft.Office.Project.Server.Library.LookupTables/MaskSequence maskSequence) cil managed

Docs.summary: Determines whether one of the text mask sequence values is used.
Docs.returns: True if is a text type of code mask.

remarks.para: The IsTextMaskSequence method returns True if the value is one of the following: NUMBER_TEXT, UPPERCASE, LOWERCASE, or CHARACTERS.
The method returns False if the value is DATE, COST, DURATION, NUMBER_DECIMAL, or FLAG.
